cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

This paper deals with image summarization and uses Convolutional Neural Networks for its implementation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a control set to produce visibly diverse images, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the algorithm, which involves measuring similarity and diversity, indicating the possibility of it being categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of bias in image summarization, which could also fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
